# Tenesta API Usage Policy

Effective Date: August 2, 2025  
Applies To: Developers, partners, and any third-party service accessing the Tenesta API.

---

## ðŸ“˜ Overview

Tenesta provides APIs to help developers, landlords, and proptech partners integrate with our platform. These APIs are intended to support authorized use only â€” such as syncing rent data, accessing payment dashboards, and automating tenant notifications.

---

## ðŸ§¾ Terms of Use

By using the Tenesta API, you agree to:

- **Authenticate** via approved tokens or keys only
- **Use only approved endpoints** documented at [docs.tenesta.com]  
- **Respect rate limits** (default: 60 requests/minute)
- **Avoid scraping** or reverse-engineering any part of the platform
- **Not share your access token** with unapproved third parties

---

## ðŸ”’ Data Privacy & Security

- All API responses are encrypted (TLS 1.2+)  
- PII (personally identifiable info) may only be stored with explicit tenant consent  
- No long-term caching of sensitive info is allowed unless part of a secure tenant-facing service

---

## Abuse and Violations

Violations of this policy may result in:

| Violation | Result |
|----------|--------|
| Exceeding rate limits | Throttling or temporary block |
| Unauthorized data scraping | API key revocation |
| Misuse of tenant or landlord data | Legal action + permanent ban |

